# Design Document

## Product: ScanStruct (formerly Snap2Sheet)

## Version: MVP (AI-powered, No Storage, One-Time Flow)

---

# 1. Design Objective

Design a mobile interface that allows users to:

> Convert any scanned image into structured, reusable key-value data using AI, exportable in multiple formats (JSON, CSV, TXT).

Key principles:

* Speed > features
* Clarity > cleverness
* Flexibility > rigid templates
* User correction > AI perfection

---

# 2. Design Philosophy

## 2.1 Core Principles

* Minimal interface
* Linear flow (no branching)
* Large touch targets
* Zero cognitive load
* Immediate feedback
* Dynamic data over fixed fields

## 2.2 UX Model

Capture → Preview → Process (OCR + AI) → Review (Dynamic Fields) → Export → Exit

No loops. No side paths.

---

# 3. Target Device

* Mobile-first
* Android priority
* Screen sizes: small to large phones
* Portrait orientation only

---

# 4. Visual Design System

## 4.1 Color Palette

| Element        | Color   |
| -------------- | ------- |
| Background     | #FFFFFF |
| Primary CTA    | #2563EB |
| Text Primary   | #111827 |
| Text Secondary | #6B7280 |
| Border         | #E5E7EB |
| Success        | #16A34A |
| Error          | #DC2626 |

## 4.2 Typography

* Font: System default (San Francisco / Roboto)
* Heading: Bold
* Body: Regular
* Button text: Semi-bold

## 4.3 Spacing System

* Base unit: 8px
* Padding: 16px / 24px
* Button height: 48–56px
